{{Infobox association | name = Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures | image = File:Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures logo.jpg | type = Academic | founded_date = 1971 | founder = | location = | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} --> | key_people = [[Jill Doerfler]] (President)<ref name="About">{{cite web |url=http://asail.org/about/ |title=About |work=ASAIL.org |publisher=Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures |accessdate=2015-03-26}}</ref> | area_served = [[United States]] and [[Canada]] | product = ''[[Studies in American Indian Literatures]]'' | focus = {{nowrap|[[Native American studies]]}} | homepage = {{URL|http://asail.org/}} }} The '''Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures''' ('''ASAIL''') is a professional academic organization. It was founded in 1971<ref name="SAIL">{{cite web |title=SAIL Publications |url=http://asail.org/sail-publications/ |work=ASAIL.org |publisher=Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures |accessdate=March 13, 2015}}</ref> to promote the study, criticism, and research of [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian]] literary traditions, both written and oral.<ref name="ASAIL">{{cite web |title=ASAIL |url=http://asail.org/ |work=ASAIL.org |publisher=Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures |accessdate=March 13, 2015}}</ref> Its journal, ''[[Studies in American Indian Literatures]]'', has been the primary journal for the study of North American indigenous literature for over thirty years.
==Conferences== ASAIL is affiliated with the [[Modern Language Association]] (MLA). ASAIL sponsors panels at several conferences:<ref name="ASAIL"/>
*The [[Native American Literature Symposium]], *The [[American Literature Association]] (ALA) conference, *The [[Society for the Study of American Women Writers]] (SSAWW) conference.
==Publications== ASAIL publishes the quarterly journal ''[[Studies in American Indian Literatures]]''.<ref name="SAIL"/> It has been the primary journal for the study of North American indigenous literature for over thirty years.<ref>{{cite news |first1=Daniel Heath |last1=Justice |first2=James H. |last2=Cox |title=From the Editors |url=http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/studies_in_american_indian_literatures/v020/20.1.justice01.html |work=[[Project MUSE]] |publisher=University of Nebraska Press |date=Spring 2008 |accessdate=March 13, 2015}}</ref>
