{{Infobox toy |name = Bilibo |image = [[File:bilibo red.jpg|220px]] |othernames = |type = |inventor = Alex Hochstrasser |country = [[Switzerland]] |company = |from = 2001 |to = present |materials = [[Plastic]] |slogan = |website = http://www.bilibo.com }} '''Bilibo''' is a "[[Seashell|shell]]-shaped, hard-wearing piece of [[plastic]]" used as a [[toy]].<ref name="indep">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/50-great-ideas-for-the-21st-century-410543.html | title=50 great ideas for the 21st century | work=[[The Independent]] | date=6 August 2006 | accessdate=30 September 2008 | author=Davis, Johnny | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080923182447/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/50-great-ideas-for-the-21st-century-410543.html| archivedate= 23 September 2008 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no|display-authors=etal}}</ref> It is produced in six different colors. It was developed in 2001 by Swiss designer Alex Hochstrasser in consultation with experts for [[child development]].
The form has been designed for children of various ages to sit comfortably in the shell whilst controlling their movements by touching the ground with their hands and feet.
According to a child's age and interests Bilibo is used as an accessory for [[Roleplay|role-]] and [[fantasy]]-play, it can be filled with objects, sand or water and emptied again or stacked. Rocking, spinning and balancing in or on the shell helps develop [[motor skills]] and the child's sense of balance. The shells are also used in [[physiotherapy]] to stimulate the [[Vestibular system|vestibular]] and [[Proprioception|proprioceptive]] systems.<ref name="official">{{cite web | url=http://www.bilibo.com/en/playing/ | title=Kids' play | publisher=Moluk | work=Bilibo | accessdate=18 November 2009}}</ref>
Children on ''[[Richard & Judy]]'' could generally be seen to prefer [[cardboard box]]es to the Bilibo, and confirmed this preference when asked.<ref name="r&j">{{cite episode | title=Friday 14th July | series=[[Richard and Judy]] | network=[[Channel 4]] | airdate=14 July 2006}}</ref>
Bilibo has received several international awards, including Spiel Gut in [[Germany]],{{Citation needed| date=February 2012}} the Swiss Product Design Award in 2002{{Citation needed| date=February 2012}} and Toy of the Year – UK Good Toy Awards in 2006.{{Citation needed| date=February 2012}}
