{{Use American English|date=August 2017}} {{Use mdy dates|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Black America | image = | image_upright = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | show_name_2 = | native_name = <!-- {{Infobox name module|language|title}} or {{Infobox name module|title}} --> | genre = [[Alternative history]] [[television drama|drama]] | creator = [[Will Packer]], [[Aaron McGruder]] | based_on = <!-- {{based on|work|author}} --> | developer = | writer = | screenplay = | story = | director = | creative_director = | presenter = <!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list --> | starring = <!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list --> | judges = <!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list --> | voices = <!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list --> | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = | language = | num_seasons = <!-- Or num_series. Increment when new seasons/series begin. See template documentation for more info. --> | num_episodes = <!-- Value is incremented when new episodes air. See template documentation for more info. --> | list_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = | location = | cinematography = | editor = <!-- Film editors --> | camera = | runtime = <!-- Reliable source required --> | company = <!-- Production companies only --> | distributor = | budget = | network = [[Amazon Video]] | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_run = <!-- The nation in which the series first aired, if different from country parameter --> | released = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | first_aired = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | related = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations --> | website = <!-- Remove or comment out this parameter line completely if URL exists on or is moved to Wikidata --> | production_website = }}
'''''Black America''''' is an upcoming [[alternative history]] [[television drama]] that imagines a nation-state formed by [[African-Americans]] called New Colonia after the [[American Civil War|Civil War]] as [[Reparations for slavery debate in the United States|reparations for slavery]]. The show is a collaboration between producer [[Will Packer]] and ''[[The Boondocks (comic strip)|The Boondocks]]'' creator [[Aaron McGruder]] for [[Amazon Video]]. McGruder is writing screenplays for the series, which has been under development for over a year as of August 2017.<ref name="NYT 8-1-17">{{cite news|author=Victor, Daniel|title=Amazon Series Imagines a New South|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=August 2, 2017|page=C3|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/01/arts/television/amazon-black-america-confederate.html|accessdate=August 3, 2017}}</ref><ref name="Deadline 8-1-17">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/black-america-amazon-alt-history-drama-will-packer-aaron-mcgruder-envisions-post-reparations-america-1202139504/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |title='Black America': Amazon Alt-History Drama From Will Packer & Aaron McGruder Envisions Post-Reparations America |date=August 1, 2017 |accessdate=August 3, 2017 |author=Andreeva, Nellie |deadurl=no}}</ref>
[[File:Aaron McGruder 2002 (cropped).png|thumb|upright=.7|McGruder in 2002]]
Central to the series's premise is the granting of three southern states — [[Louisiana]], [[Mississippi]] and [[Alabama]] — to freed slaves as [[Reparations for slavery|reparations]] after the [[American Civil War|Civil War]].<ref name="NYT 8-1-17"/>
The announcement of the in-development series came in response to [[HBO]]'s announcement of its own upcoming series ''[[Confederate (TV series)|Confederate]]'', which posits a different alternate history branching from the Civil War period.<ref name="NYT 8-1-17"/><ref name="Deadline 8-1-17"/> Both series are set in the modern day.<ref name="Deadline 8-1-17"/>
