{{italic title}}
<!-- Discuss before changing this to an infobox. This is a painting with a lot of intricate detail and looks like an incomprehensible smear at infobox default size -->[[File:Jacob van Ruisdael Vue d'Amsterdam.jpg||right|upright=1.8|thumb|''View of the Binnenamstel at Amsterdam'' |alt=Painting of a city scene with a river]]

'''''View of the Binnenamstel at Amsterdam''''' is a 17th-century [[oil painting|oil]] on canvas painting by the [[Dutch Golden Age painting|Dutch Golden Age painter]] [[Jacob van Ruisdael]]. It is in the collection of the [[Museum of Fine Arts in Budapest]].{{sfn|Slive|2001|p=15}}

The painting is catalogue number 15 in the 1911 catalogue raisonné by art historian [[Hofstede de Groot]]. He wrote "The spectator looks towards the old Jachthaven and the Blaauwbrug, from the canal-bank where the Deaconesses' Home for Old Women was erected later." {{sfn|Hofstede de Groot|1911|p=12}} The painting is catalogue number 2 in [[Seymour Slive]]'s 2001 catalogue raisonné of Ruisdael.{{sfn|Slive|2001|p=15}} Its inventory number for the Museum of Fine Arts is 4278 .<ref>{{cite web|title=View of the Binnenamstel at Amsterdam|url=http://www.szepmuveszeti.hu/adatlap_eng/view_of_the_binnenamstel_in_8575|publisher=[[Museum of Fine Arts in Budapest]]|accessdate=1 February 2016}}</ref> 

Its dimensions are 52.5 cm x 43.5 cm.{{sfn|Slive|2001|p=15}} 

